<task id="027" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>Add factory config keys to 8 sibling integration fixtures — absorb 98 Cluster B failures</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, integration, fixture-config, scope-absorption, p23-i</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-I-followup</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Edits 8 sibling fixture files in `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/`. Each fixture has global blast radius across the tests that inherit it — analogous to NFR-07 anti-parallelism guard but distributed across 8 files. Runs in single-agent sequence to avoid agent-level test-run conflicts and preserve clean delta measurement.</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Task 062 (Wave 2.4) discovered that 98 of 108 remaining integration failures trace to
    8 sibling fixtures in `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` that inherit
    `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;` DIRECTLY rather than `IntegrationTestFixture`.
    Each missing config keys necessary for `Program.cs` host build to succeed (same
    `CosmosPersistence:Endpoint` + `SpeAdmin:KeyVaultUri` + possibly `AgentService:*`
    pattern as task 018's CustomWebAppFactory fix and task 060's WorkspaceTestFixture fix).

    Apply the SAME minimum-viable repair pattern to each sibling fixture. Per task 062's
    handoff: prefer (b) refactor each fixture to inherit `IntegrationTestFixture` (1-LOC
    class declaration change per file) IF the inheritance hierarchy supports it cleanly;
    otherwise (a) copy the necessary dict entries (additive).

    Per owner directive 2026-05-31 ("absorb deviations, do not defer"): this task delivers
    the integration-fixture absorption within Phase 2+3 rather than deferring to a separate
    project.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent applying the canonical fixture-config-key pattern across 8 sibling integration test fixtures.</role>

  <goal>
    The 8 sibling fixtures provide the same Cosmos/Agent/SpeAdmin config keys
    that `IntegrationTestFixture.cs` provides, OR inherit from it directly. Each fixture's
    associated tests run without `Program.cs:107` host-build errors. Cluster B (98 SpeAdmin
    failures across 8 classes) is fully cleared OR reclassified per §6.2.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="discovery">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/notes/handoffs/integration-fixture-sibling-discovery-2026-05-31.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-062-evidence">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-062-2026-05-31.trx</file>
