  <steps>
    <step order="1">Locate the 8 fixtures via Glob: `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/**/{SemanticSearch,RecordSearch,KnowledgeBase,Analysis,ChatEndpoints,ReAnalysisFlow,Authorization}TestFixture.cs`. Record actual paths (the discovery doc estimates Fixtures/ subdirectory but verify).</step>

    <step order="2">Read `tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/IntegrationTestFixture.cs` and note the exact config keys it provides + its public surface (constructor, properties, IClassFixture compatibility).</step>

    <step order="3">For each of the 8 sibling fixtures: READ the file. Determine:
      (a) does it already inherit from `IntegrationTestFixture`? — if yes, skip (already fixed by 062)
      (b) does it inherit from `WebApplicationFactory&lt;Program&gt;` directly? — apply fix
      (c) does it have any incompatible state that prevents inheritance? — if so, fall back to copying dict entries

      Document the decision per fixture in the delta report.
    </step>

    <step order="4">Pre-edit baseline: `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ -c Release --logger:"trx;LogFileName=pre-027-baseline.trx" --results-directory projects/.../baseline/` — expected: 422 / 262 pass / 108 fail / 52 skip (matches post-062 state). 15 min timebox.</step>

    <step order="5">Apply fixes one fixture at a time. For each:
      - Preferred: change class declaration to `: IntegrationTestFixture` (inheritance)
      - Fallback: copy the 7 dict entries from `IntegrationTestFixture.cs` (additive)
      - After each fixture edit: `dotnet build tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` — confirm 0 errors before proceeding to next
    </step>

    <step order="6">Post-all-edits build: `dotnet build tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/` → 0 errors expected.</step>

    <step order="7">Post-edit full test run: `dotnet test tests/integration/Spe.Integration.Tests/ -c Release --logger:"trx;LogFileName=post-027-measure.trx"` (timebox 30 min). Expected: ~108 → ~10 failures (−98 if all clusters clear cleanly).</step>

    <step order="8">If any of the 8 fixtures' associated tests STILL fail after the fix, that's a non-config root cause. Triage per §6.2 (`repaired` if line-level fix possible without §4.8 escalation; `real-bug-pending-fix` if production bug surfaces; `flaky-quarantined` if non-deterministic).</step>

    <step order="9">Write `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/post-027-delta-2026-05-31.md` documenting:
      - Pre (108) → post (NNN) count
      - Per-fixture decision (inheritance vs. copy)
      - Cluster B disposition: how many of the 98 were cleared
      - Any tests classified `real-bug-pending-fix` or `flaky-quarantined` with ledger references
      - Phase 2+3 integration-tier net failure remaining (input to Wave 2.5 + final validation)
    </step>

    <step order="10">Update task 027 POML `&lt;status&gt;` to `completed` with `&lt;completion-notes&gt;`. Update `current-task.md`.</step>

    <step order="11">Step 9.5 Quality Gates (FULL rigor): code-review (each fixture edit) + adr-check + lint. Document in current-task.md.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Glob">locate sibling fixtures</tool>
    <tool name="Read">fixtures + IntegrationTestFixture for pattern</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">apply the 8 fixture fixes</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">build + test + TRX capture</tool>
    <tool name="Write">delta report</tool>
  </tools>

